<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="486" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[2059,2652,1546,1970]" pageId="5" pageNumber="486">
This species has often been recognized as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1858" box="[2326,2477,1735,1773]" class="Mammalia" family="Phalangeridae" genus="Strigocuscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diprotodontia" pageId="5" pageNumber="486" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="celebensis">S. celebensis</taxonomicName>
in the past. Studies of possible taxonomic distinctions of populations from the islands of Siau (= Siao) and Sangir (= Greater Sangihe) are needed. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="486" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6657437" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6657437" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6657437/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="486" targetBox="[1444,2035,1553,1966]" targetPageId="5">
